Description: Oval handle of a pottery transport amphora at neck join to sharpish turn. Red paint. Fractional jar?. Clay fine ginger-buff. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 201, 28. Name Diodotos. There were two fabricants of the name Diodotos, whose careers may have overlapped; see I. Nicolaou, Paphos V, 2005, 157.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1705)
